    "exp": "Correct answers (in order):\n\n[1] Cisco-NX-OS-device:System\n    RESTCONF root (capital S).\n\n[2] intf-items/phys-items\n    YANG path to physical interfaces.\n\n[3] accept: application/yang.data+json\n    NX-OS uses DOT (yang.data), not hyphen.\n\n[4] expert:'1234QWer!'\n    Basic Auth credentials for RESTCONF.\n\n[5] select(.mtu >= 9000)\n    jq client-side filter. Note the DOT before mtu (.mtu) — required in jq.\n    >= is greater-than-or-equal in jq.\n\n✅ Full correct command:\ncurl -sk \"https://192.168.89.73/restconf/data/Cisco-NX-OS-device:System/intf-items/phys-items\" \\\n  -H 'accept: application/yang.data+json' \\\n  -u expert:'1234QWer!' \\\n  | jq '.\"phys-items\".\"PhysIf-list\"[] | select(.mtu >= 9000) | {id, mtu}'\n\nDistractors:\n  Cisco-NX-OS-device:system → lowercase s fails\n  yang-data+json → IOS-XE format; NX-OS uses yang.data\n  select(.mtu > 9000) → strictly greater, misses mtu=9000\n  select(.mtu == 9000) → exact match only\n  select(mtu >= 9000) → missing leading dot; jq requires .mtu\n  Cookie: APIC-cookie → DME auth, not RESTCONF\n\nU0001f9ea How to test in real-time:\n  Option A: Browse https://192.168.89.73 → Method=RESTCONF (Yang), json\n  Option B: Use YangSuite with Cisco-NX-OS-device module",
