    "exp": "Correct answers (in order):\n\n[1] l1PhysIf.json\n    Physical interface class.\n\n[2] and\n    DME logical operator combining multiple conditions.\n\n[3] eq(l1PhysIf.adminSt,\"up\")\n    Admin status equals \"up\" (lowercase!).\n\n[4] eq(l1PhysIf.operSt,\"up\")\n    Oper status equals \"up\" (lowercase!).\n\n[5] ge(l1PhysIf.mtu,\"9000\")\n    MTU >= 9000.\n\n[6] Cookie: APIC-cookie=$token\n    DME auth.\n\n⚠️ Conditions [3]-[5] inside and() are order-independent — any arrangement is correct.\n\n✅ Full correct command:\ncurl -sk \"https://192.168.89.73/api/class/l1PhysIf.json?query-target-filter=and(eq(l1PhysIf.adminSt,\\\"up\\\"),eq(l1PhysIf.operSt,\\\"up\\\"),ge(l1PhysIf.mtu,\\\"9000\\\"))\" \\\n  -H \"Cookie: APIC-cookie=$token\" \\\n  | jq '.imdata[].l1PhysIf.attributes | {id, adminSt, operSt, mtu}'\n\nDistractors:\n  or → would match interfaces where ANY condition is true\n  eq(l1PhysIf.adminSt,\"Up\") → case-sensitive! DME uses lowercase \"up\", not \"Up\"\n  gt(l1PhysIf.mtu,...) → strictly greater-than, misses mtu=9000\n  eq(l1PhysIf.mtu,...) → exact match only\n\nU0001f9ea How to test in real-time:\n  1. Browse https://192.168.89.73/visore.html\n  2. Search class: l1PhysIf — check adminSt, operSt, mtu values\n  3. Note: adminSt/operSt values are lowercase (\"up\"/\"down\")",
