    "exp": "Correct answers (in order):\n\n[1] Cisco-NX-OS-device:System\n    RESTCONF root.\n\n[2] intf-items/phys-items\n    YANG path to physical interfaces.\n\n[3] accept: application/yang.data+json\n    NX-OS RESTCONF accept header (dot format).\n\n[4] expert:'1234QWer!'\n    Basic Auth credentials.\n\n[5] select(.adminSt == \"up\" and .operSt == \"up\" and .mtu >= 9000)\n    jq client-side filter combining three conditions with 'and'.\n    • Leading dot required: .adminSt, .operSt, .mtu\n    • String comparison uses == with quotes: == \"up\"\n    • Numeric comparison: .mtu >= 9000 (no quotes around 9000 in jq)\n    • Case-sensitive: \"up\" not \"Up\"\n\n✅ Full correct command:\ncurl -sk \"https://192.168.89.73/restconf/data/Cisco-NX-OS-device:System/intf-items/phys-items\" \\\n  -H 'accept: application/yang.data+json' \\\n  -u expert:'1234QWer!' \\\n  | jq '.\"phys-items\".\"PhysIf-list\"[] | select(.adminSt == \"up\" and .operSt == \"up\" and .mtu >= 9000) | {id, adminSt, operSt, mtu}'\n\nDistractors:\n  select(... == \"Up\") → case-sensitive; RESTCONF returns lowercase \"up\"\n  select(... or ...) → 'or' matches if ANY condition true; need 'and' for ALL\n  select(adminSt == ...) → missing leading dots; jq requires .adminSt\n  Cisco-NX-OS-device:system → lowercase s fails\n\nU0001f9ea How to test in real-time:\n  Option A: Browse https://192.168.89.73 → Method=RESTCONF (Yang), json\n  Option B: Use YangSuite with Cisco-NX-OS-device module",
