    "scenario": "",
    "exp": "Correct answers:\n\n✅ Option C is correct.\n\nWhy C is correct:\n• Double bd-items nesting: bd-items → bd-items → BD-list\n  The YANG tree shows TWO levels of bd-items before BD-list. Both are required.\n• BD-list and PhysIf-list are JSON arrays [...]\n  YANG lists MUST be JSON arrays, even for a single entry. Objects {} are invalid.\n• List keys present: fabEncap (BD-list key) and id (PhysIf-list key) are mandatory.\n• intf-items wrapper: phys-items lives UNDER intf-items, not directly under System.\n\nWhy others are wrong:\n\n❌ Option A — Missing inner bd-items\n  Goes bd-items → BD-list directly, skipping the second bd-items level.\n  YANG tree clearly shows: bd-items → bd-items → BD-list (two levels).\n\n❌ Option B — YANG lists as objects {} instead of arrays []\n  BD-list: {} and PhysIf-list: {} are objects.\n  YANG lists MUST be JSON arrays: BD-list: [...] and PhysIf-list: [...]\n  Even with a single entry, the array wrapper is required.\n\n❌ Option D — Two errors:\n  1. Missing intf-items wrapper: phys-items is placed directly under System.\n     YANG tree shows: System → intf-items → phys-items → PhysIf-list.\n  2. Missing id key in PhysIf-list. The list key (id=eth1/13) is mandatory.\n\n✅ Full correct curl command:\ncurl --request PATCH \\\n  --url https://192.168.89.73/restconf/data/Cisco-NX-OS-device:System \\\n  --header 'accept: application/yang.data+json' \\\n  --header 'authorization: Basic ZXhwZXJ0OjEyMzRRV2VyIQ==' \\\n  --header 'content-type: application/yang.data+json' \\\n  --data '{\"bd-items\":{\"bd-items\":{\"BD-list\":[{\"fabEncap\":\"vlan-300\",\"name\":\"TestVLAN-300\"}]}},\"intf-items\":{\"phys-items\":{\"PhysIf-list\":[{\"id\":\"eth1/13\",\"accessVlan\":\"vlan-300\",\"mtu\":9216}]}}}'\n\nU0001f9ea How to test in real-time:\n  Option A: Browse https://192.168.89.73 → Method=RESTCONF (Yang), json, use PATCH\n  Option B: Use YangSuite → navigate Cisco-NX-OS-device:System → bd-items and intf-items",
